data.name: DBMania
data.description:
Hi masters of technology! B-)
Here's a preview for the main event. Starting from 18th March, 3 to 4 questions will be posted on each day. Text us your answers. Leader board will be maintained and top scorers at the end of the event stand a chance to win exciting goodies @ aBaCUS'17! :D 
Register yourself at www.abacus.org.in before you begin! :)
Rules and Format:
1) aBaCUS id is a MUST.
2) Questions will be posted at 5.00 PM everyday.
3) Send your answers to +91 9655883077.
4) Message format should be:
Name
College Name
aBaCUS id (MUST)
department, year
(finally :P) your answer!
5) Scores will be awarded based on speed and correctness of your answer.
6) Only the first answer from a participant will be counted. 
7) Anybody who comments the answer will be disqualified from further rounds.
8) Updated Leader board will be uploaded on the next day at 10.00 AM
Get ready to play the tech-fusion!

data.name: Invitation for August Challenge 2015 | CodeChef
data.description:
Hello Everyone :) 

CodeChef invites you to participate in August Long Challenge at https://www.codechef.com/AUG15. As always, the long contests will start on first Friday of every month and last for 10 days. This ensures that two weekends are covered.

Here are the details:

Start Date: Friday, 7th August, 2015 3:00 PM (IST)
End Date: Monday, 17th August, 2015 3:00 PM (IST)
Check your timezone: http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=CodeChef+August+Long+Challenge&iso=20150807T13&p1=44

Prizes:

For Indians:

1st prize: INR 12000
2nd prize: INR 8000

For Rest of the world:

1st prize: $400
2nd prize: $300

In addition to the above prizes. Top 10 global, Top 20 Indian, Top 5 school (Indian), Top 5 school (Global), Top 3 challenge problem solvers Indian and Global (apart from the winners) get cool CodeChef goodies. Starting with August Challenge 2015, top 5  girl coders will be provided with goodies, given that they are among top 100 in the final ranklist (this will be irrespective of the region).

It promises to deliver on an interesting set of algorithmic problems with something for all. 

Good Luck! Hope to see you participating!!

data.name: Workshop on Cyber Security and Brain Hacking
data.description: infYSEC, A globally recognized information Security Services Organization, that holds the GUINNESS record for the world’s largest Hackathon, is set to conduct a workshop on Computer and Brain Hacking! The Internet of Things is a vision of the future but not for long. With more than 25 billion connections already, the future is fast becoming reality. To keep up with the change, we bring you a workshop dedicated to IoT and cyber security in the modern times. Along with that, get inducted into the basics and practicalities of Humanhacking. Understand the complexities of the human brain and learn what it takes to hack it too!

data.name: The T+ Run
data.description:
An unprecedented run organised by students of Anna University to aid Project LEAP, an initiative by Becoming I Foundation as a part of Techofes+, a Techofes 2015 Social Outreach initiative.

Project LEAP is a one-of-a-kind project which aims to change the way primary education happens in low income classrooms.

Day and Date: Sunday, 01-02-2015
Distances: 6KM  |  10KM
Venue: CEG, Anna University
Assembly time: 05:00 AM

Register at: plus.techofes.in/run
